notice info-notice\">\n<p>It’s your responsibility to make sure payments reach <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> on <a href=\"/prepare-file-annual-accounts-for-limited-company\" title=\"Corporation Tax deadlines\">time</a> - there are <a href=\"/prepare-file-annual-accounts-for-limited-company/penalties\" title=\"Corporation Tax penalties\">penalties</a> if you don’t.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Your Corporation Tax payment reference number</h2>\n\n<p>You must use the 17-character Corporation Tax payment reference number specific to the period you&rsquo;re paying. Your payment will be delayed if you don&rsquo;t. You can find it on your payslip or through your company&rsquo;s <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://online.hmrc.gov.uk/corporation-tax/\" title=\"Corporation Tax online\"><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> online account.</a> or by calling <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>. </p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong>Corporation Tax payment reference enquiries</strong><br />\n01236 785057  <br />\nMonday to Friday, 9am to 4pm</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Online and telephone banking, Bacs or CHAPS</h2>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Check your bank’s transaction limits and processing times.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The back of your payslip tells you which <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> account to use. If you&rsquo;re not sure, use Cumbernauld. You must use your Corporation Tax payment reference number </p>\n\n<p>If you want to pay by CHAPS, you can fill in an instruction to your bank online. CHAPS payments usually reach <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> the same day if your bank sends them between 9am and 3pm.</p>\n\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Account name</th>\n      <th>Sort code</th>\n      <th>Account number</th>\n      <th>CHAPS instruction</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td><abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abb